<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB03682</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT PROVIDING FOR AN EARLY OPTIONAL RETIREMENT FOR DISABLED PERSONS WORKING IN GOVERNMENT</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : States that all disabled persons working in government, who are members of the Government Service Insurance System, are entitled to the benefits under Section 13 of Republic Act 8291 otherwise known as “the Government Service Insurance System Act of 1997” provided that he or she: a) Has rendered at least 15 years of service; b) Has been suffering a disability for at least 10 years immediately preceding the retirement; and c) Is at least fifty five (55) years of age at the time of retirement.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : “The Persons With Disability Retirement Act of 2019.”</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ROMUALDEZ, FERDINAND MARTIN G., ROMUALDEZ, YEDDA MARIE K.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-08-08</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Tambunting (000 2019-09-19)</td><td>2. Sy-Alvarado (000 2019-11-06)</td><tr><td>3. Olivarez (000 2020-02-13)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON PERSONS WITH DISABILITIES ON 2020-01-21</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PREVIOUS COMMITTEE REFERRALS :PRIMARILY REFERRED TO SOCIAL SERVICES on 2019-08-14;</td></tr></table>